I put the enginefacase.configure() call in a try/except block and everything was able to pass for me locally.

And after this patch, my patch to break out functional tests into their own run work. I was tracking that failure down last night and had run out of time just as I was starting to look into the enginefacade changes, so great to see this.

Octave, if you are tied up with other things and would like me to update this with the exception handling let me know. I think we either just need to make sure it only runs the first time, or ignore the failure for subsequent calls.
